@startuml
title Login e Refresh — Token Opaco + Cookie HttpOnly
autonumber
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Usuário interno" as User
participant "Frontend React/Vite" as Frontend
participant "API Express\n/auth" as API
participant "AuthService" as Auth
database "SQLite atual\n(PostgreSQL futuro)" as DB
participant "Auditoria técnica" as Audit

User -> Frontend : informa login/senha
Frontend -> API : POST /auth/login
API -> Auth : login(payload, req)
Auth -> DB : busca usuario_interno
Auth -> Auth : valida senha e status
Auth -> Auth : gera access token opaco
Auth -> DB : grava auth_session.token_hash
Auth -> Auth : gera refresh token opaco
Auth -> DB : grava auth_refresh_token.token_hash
Auth -> Audit : auth_login
Auth --> API : access token + refreshCookie
API --> Frontend : JSON com bearer\nSet-Cookie academia_sa_refresh
note right of API
Cookie:
HttpOnly
SameSite=Lax
Secure apenas em production
path=/auth
end note

Frontend -> API : GET /auth/me\nAuthorization: Bearer access
API -> Auth : resolveSessionToken(access)
Auth -> DB : valida hash em auth_session
API --> Frontend : usuário autenticado

== Renovação ==
Frontend -> API : POST /auth/refresh\nCookie HttpOnly
API -> Auth : refresh(req)
Auth -> DB : valida refresh ativo
Auth -> Auth : gera novo access token opaco
Auth -> DB : atualiza auth_session.token_hash\n(access anterior deixa de valer)
Auth -> Auth : gera novo refresh token opaco
Auth -> DB : refresh antigo -> rotacionado\nnovo refresh -> ativo
Auth -> Audit : auth_refresh
Auth --> API : novo access + novo refreshCookie
API --> Frontend : JSON com novo bearer\nSet-Cookie novo refresh

== Reuso bloqueado ==
Frontend -> API : POST /auth/refresh\nCookie antigo rotacionado
API -> Auth : refresh(req)
Auth -> DB : detecta refresh não ativo
Auth -> DB : marca refresh como reutilizado
Auth -> DB : revoga família de refresh tokens\ne sessão relacionada
Auth -> Audit : auth_refresh_reuse_detected
API --> Frontend : 401 REFRESH_TOKEN_REUTILIZADO
@enduml
